# Patch 01: Browser-First Meeting Detection
# Target: watcher.py (in trnscrb package)
#
# PROBLEM:
# trnscrb's default watcher checks for native meeting apps (Zoom.app,
# Microsoft Teams.app) first. Most users join calls via browser, so
# native-only detection misses the majority of meetings.
#
# CHANGE:
# In the `detect_meeting()` function (or equivalent meeting detection logic):
#
# 1. Add a new function `_browser_has_meeting_tab()` that checks running
#    browsers (Safari, Chrome, Arc, Firefox) for meeting-related URLs:
#    - meet.google.com
#    - zoom.us/j/ or zoom.us/wc/
#    - teams.microsoft.com
#    - app.gather.town
#    - whereby.com
#
#    Use AppleScript to query browser tabs:
#      osascript -e 'tell application "Google Chrome" to get URL of active tab of front window'
#    Or for Safari:
#      osascript -e 'tell application "Safari" to get URL of current tab of front window'
#
# 2. In `detect_meeting()`, call `_browser_has_meeting_tab()` BEFORE
#    checking for native apps. Return True if any browser tab matches.
#
# 3. The detection order should be:
#    a) Browser tabs (Meet, Zoom web, Teams web)
#    b) Native apps (Zoom.app, Teams.app, FaceTime, etc.)
#    c) System audio level threshold (fallback)
#
# WHY:
# Browser-first detection catches 90%+ of calls. Without this patch,
# trnscrb only starts recording when it sees a native app, missing
# browser-based calls entirely.
